20:26.980 --> 20:28.500
Hey. Whoa.

20:28.700 --> 20:29.980
Sorry.

20:30.180 --> 20:32.060
[Teddy panting]

20:32.250 --> 20:34.300
I'm sorry.

20:36.400 --> 20:38.990
I think I was having
a bad dream.

20:39.190 --> 20:41.690
[sighs]

20:41.890 --> 20:43.650
I know you don't want
to leave, but...

20:44.580 --> 20:46.410
...after this, I don't think
you can stay here.

20:46.610 --> 20:49.240
So I can help you find a place,

20:49.440 --> 20:51.520
if you'd rather not be with me.

20:51.720 --> 20:53.520
For how long?

20:53.720 --> 20:55.180
Till Franklin's dead.

20:55.380 --> 20:57.700
So that's what happens now?

20:57.900 --> 21:00.010
You kill Franklin?

21:00.210 --> 21:02.570
And then what?

21:02.770 --> 21:06.710
I'm not good with having my fate
in someone else's hands.

21:06.910 --> 21:09.360
If you and I are going
to continue this...

21:10.610 --> 21:14.370
...I need to know how you see
things playing out from here.

21:14.570 --> 21:16.270
It depends.

21:17.890 --> 21:19.410
PARISSA:
On what?

21:26.730 --> 21:28.760
On what you want.

21:30.450 --> 21:32.220
I keep looking around my life,

21:32.420 --> 21:35.080
and I got no one.

21:35.280 --> 21:37.880
The one bright spot
in all of it is you.

21:38.080 --> 21:39.050
What do you want?

21:39.250 --> 21:41.260
You want to leave?

21:42.470 --> 21:43.640
Do you want to take the money

21:43.840 --> 21:46.060
and we'll figure out
how to use it? That's fine.

21:47.470 --> 21:50.130
I'm done giving up things
for them.

21:54.650 --> 21:56.480
What do you want?

21:56.680 --> 21:58.830
PARISSA:
I'm going to be honest.

21:59.030 --> 22:01.010
That might be the sexiest thing

22:01.210 --> 22:04.320
a man has ever said to me
in my entire life.

22:15.600 --> 22:17.780
[vehicle approaching]

22:19.810 --> 22:21.820
[brakes squeaking]

22:29.340 --> 22:31.480
GUSTAVO: You're
a difficult man to reach.

22:31.680 --> 22:33.450
Yeah, I've been busy.

22:33.650 --> 22:35.450
So I heard.

22:39.490 --> 22:43.150
Look, I'm guessing Teddy's not
too happy with me right now.

22:43.350 --> 22:44.500
He'd probably give you
anything you want

22:44.700 --> 22:46.980
to help set me up, right?

22:47.180 --> 22:50.330
Problems I got, you're the only
one who can solve them.

22:51.980 --> 22:54.820
What you need
to get this done, Oso?

22:55.020 --> 22:56.650
You said ten million.

22:56.850 --> 22:58.890
- I did say that, yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

22:59.090 --> 23:00.820
